IF:

if test expression:
    statement(s)
    
if test expression is True then statements are executed. Otherwise not. 
Intendation is a start and non intendetion is the end. 

IF...ELSE:

if test expression:
    Body of if
else:
    Body of else
    
For True if is executed and for False else is executed. 

IF...ElIF...ELSE:

if test expression:
    Body of if
elif test expression:
    Body of elif
else: 
    Body of else
    
    
If True then body executed.
If False then Elif tested, True executed, False goes to else. 
Can have many elif. 

Nesting: 
num = float(input("Enter a number: "))
if num >= 0:
    if num == 0:
        print("Zero")
    else:
        print("Positive number")
else:
    print("Negative number")
    
    
